HEADWORD: Trimorph
<hw>Tri"morph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Trimorphous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>A substance
which crystallizes in three distinct forms, or which has three distinct
physical states; also, any one of these distinct forms. See
<er>Trimorphism</er>, 1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

